article.description: — Darlinstone Dubar's 24 points helped Hofstra defeat Northeastern 82-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Dubar's 24 lead Hofstra over Northeastern 82-62
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- — Darlinstone Dubar's 24 points helped Hofstra defeat Northeastern 82-62 on Saturday. Dubar shot 10 for 16, including 4 for 7 from beyond the arc for the Pride (16-11, 9-5 Coastal Athletic Association). German Plotnikov shot 7 for 9, including 4 for 5 from beyond the arc to add 20 points. Tyler Thomas shot 6 for 14 (3 for 8 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line to finish with 18 points. The Huskies (10-17, 5-9) were led in scoring by Luka Sakota, who finished with 13 points. Chris Doherty added 12 points for Northeastern. Masai Troutman also had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
